Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: badRequestException
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: A client error occurred when the stream was created. Check the parameters of the request and try your request again.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: conflictException
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: A new stream started with the same session ID. The current stream has been terminated.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: internalFailureException
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: A problem occurred while processing the audio. Amazon Transcribe terminated processing.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: limitExceededException
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: Your client has exceeded one of the Amazon Transcribe limits, typically the limit on audio length. Break your audio stream into smaller chunks and try your request again.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: transcriptEvent
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: A portion of the transcription of the audio stream. Events are sent periodically from Amazon Transcribe to your application. The event can be a partial transcription of a section of the audio stream, or it can be the entire transcription of that portion of the audio stream.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: transcript
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: The transcription of the audio stream. The transcription is composed of all of the items in the results list.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: results
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: Result objects that contain the results of transcribing a portion of the input audio stream. The array can be empty.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: languageCode
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: The language code for the input audio stream.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: mediaEncoding
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: The encoding used for the input audio stream.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: mediaSampleRateHertz
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: The sample rate for the input audio stream. Use 8000 Hz for low quality audio and 16000 Hz for high quality audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: sessionId
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: An identifier for a specific transcription session.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: transcriptResultStream
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: Represents the stream of transcription events from Amazon Transcribe to your application.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: vocabularyName
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: The name of the vocabulary used when processing the job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: audioStream
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: PCM-encoded stream of audio blobs. The audio stream is encoded as an HTTP2 data frame.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: languageCode
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: Indicates the language used in the input audio stream.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: mediaEncoding
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: The encoding used for the input audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: mediaSampleRateHertz
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: The sample rate, in Hertz, of the input audio. We suggest that you use 8000 Hz for low quality audio and 16000 Hz for high quality audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: sessionId
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: A identifier for the transcription session. Use this parameter when you want to retry a session. If you don’t provide a session ID, Amazon Transcribe will generate one for you and return it in the response.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.name: vocabularyName
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingStartStrea.abstract: The name of the vocabulary to use when processing the transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.name: alternatives
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.abstract: A list of possible transcriptions for the audio. Each alternative typically contains one item that contains the result of the transcription.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.name: endTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.abstract: The offset in milliseconds from the beginning of the audio stream to the end of the result.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.name: isPartial
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.abstract: true to indicate that Amazon Transcribe has additional transcription data to send, false to indicate that this is the last transcription result for the audio stream.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.name: startTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.abstract: The offset in milliseconds from the beginning of the audio stream to the beginning of the result.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.name: content
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.abstract: The word or punctuation that was recognized in the input audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.name: endTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.abstract: The offset from the beginning of the audio stream to the end of the audio that resulted in the item.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.name: startTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.abstract: The offset from the beginning of the audio stream to the beginning of the audio that resulted in the item.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.name: types
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html#.abstract: The type of the item. PRONUNCIATION indicates that the item is a word that was recognized in the input audio. PUNCTUATION indicates that the item was interpreted as a pause in the input audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioStrea.name: audioEvent
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioStrea.abstract: A blob of audio from your application. You audio stream consists of one or more audio events.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioEvent.name: audioChunk
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioEvent.abstract: An audio blob that contains the next part of the audio that you want to transcribe.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAlternativ.name: items
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAlternativ.abstract: One or more alternative interpretations of the input audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAlternativ.name: transcript
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAlternativ.abstract: The text that was transcribed from the audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAlternativ.name: AWSTranscribeStreamingAlternative
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAlternativ.abstract: A list of possible transcriptions for the audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioEvent.name: AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioEvent
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioEvent.abstract: Provides a wrapper for the audio chunks that you are sending.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioStrea.name: AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioStream
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingAudioStrea.abstract: Represents the audio stream from your application to Amazon Transcribe.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html.name: AWSTranscribeStreamingItem
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingItem.html.abstract: A word or phrase transcribed from the input audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.name: AWSTranscribeStreamingResult
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingResult.htm.abstract: The result of transcribing a portion of the input audio stream.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscriptEvent
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: Represents a set of transcription results from the server to the client. It contains one or more segments of the transcription.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.name: AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscriptResultStream
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreamingTranscript.abstract: Represents the transcription result stream from Amazon Transcribe to your application.

Classes/AWSTranscribeStreaming.html.name: AWSTranscribeStreaming
Classes/AWSTranscribeStreaming.html.abstract: Operations and objects for transcribing streaming speech to text.
